Yes — I can see the actual issue now.

You did not necessarily mess up the YAML logic. The failure is from Bash scope.

This line runs the function in a subshell:

CONTROLLER_VARS_FILE="$(write_controller_vars_file)"

So this assignment inside write_controller_vars_file() does not survive back into the main script:

GENERATED_GROUP_VARS_SOURCE_FILE="${generated_group_vars_tmp}"

That is why you get:

ERROR: Generated group vars source file was not set

The fix is: create GENERATED_GROUP_VARS_SOURCE_FILE in the main flow before calling write_controller_vars_file(), then let the function write to that already-known file.

